<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-630-726  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 630 726.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Sept 4 1989 n554 p26(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New science office role?andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Van Nostrand, Jim.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Congress is considering a Senate bill which would direct the WhiteHouse Office of Science and Technology Policy to find ways ofbetter determining the threat to national security posed bydeclining US industrial competitiveness.andP;  The proposal wouldrequire the office to assemble a panel of experts to submit abiennial national critical technologies report identifying up to30 technologies judged most essential to long-term US nationalsecurity and economic prosperity.andP;  'Dual-use technology,' whichties military and commercial technologies closely together, is akey theme of the Senate bill.andP;  Engineering design, applicationsengineering, and other downstream activities are crucial in thesetechnologies, and experts note that current defense procurementpolicy tends to isolate military markets from commercial ones.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     CompetitionEngineeringSecurityGovernment RegulationUnited States. Congress.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>